                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.113 Airplanes/1: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-07-30T17:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 30, 1926—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 30—10 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>309. My telegram 162, April 3, 2 p.m. I am reliably informed that the British
                    Government has recently removed commercial aeroplanes from the list of articles
                    procured under the arms embargo and that Avro machines are now being offered for
                    sale in China by representatives of British interests.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
